<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In ZF1 this header was named "MIME-Version". In ZF2 this has been changed to "Mime-Version". Mail headers are case-insensitive, but who knows how many buggy clients are out there and the RFC uses "MIME-Version", too: <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045">http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045</a></p>

<p>The affected methods are "getFieldName" and "toString".</p>

